GDPR AND DATA PROTECTION

The Software implements GDPR-by-design architecture. Any authorized deployment
must maintain the following invariants required by EU Regulation 2016/679:
  - Content is never logged (Art. 5(1)(c) data minimisation)
  - All writes to persistent storage are atomic (Art. 5(1)(f) integrity)
  - Right to erasure (Art. 17) is preserved via purge_before() in logger.py
  - No PII in Redis beyond HMAC/Fernet-encrypted tokens (Art. 32)

Violation of these invariants by an authorized licensee constitutes a material
breach of the license agreement.

